					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13973703</guid>
				<title>SCP-5134</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13973703/scp-5134</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 09 Jan 2021 22:01:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Kilroy137</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>7051578</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Interesting concept, but there isn't really that much there that makes it an SCP. I believe there is a list of anomalous items that don't have enough properties to really be a full-blown SCP article. It could be pretty good over there. I like the idea, but the execution could use some touching-up.</p> <p>I also feel like the containment procedures are extremely overdone. If it can be safely kept in a box, the foundation will put it in a box. or, more accurately, a secured locker. If the pedestal isn't necessary for containment, it shouldn't be there. If it is, explain why. The clinical tone could use quite a bit of work too.</p> <p>If you really want this to be an SCP, I recommend working on it to try to make it better for being used for storytelling purposes.</p> <p>I've also realized that this SCP's clearance requirements are way too high given it's anomalous abilities. The O-5 have much bigger fish to fry than someone wanting a book to have their name in it. And level-4 clearance requirements are also too high. Level 4-clearance is considered Top-Secret. This is something that you really don't want the most important people in the foundation touching, as it gives their enemies a nice little list of everyone important in the foundation and their names.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
